\begin_layout Enumerate
The solutions in the three region I (
\begin_inset Formula $x<x'$
\end_inset

), II (
\begin_inset Formula $x'\leq x\leq x'+\Delta x$
\end_inset

), and III (
\begin_inset Formula $x>x'+\Delta x$
\end_inset

) satisfy 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{A}g_{\mbox{I,III}}=0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\hat{A}g_{\mbox{II}}=1/\Delta x$
\end_inset

.
 Given the hint and the fact that they must vanish at 
\begin_inset Formula $x=0,L$
\end_inset

, this means that they must be of the form: 
\begin_inset Formula \[
g_{\mbox{I}}=\alpha(e^{\kappa x}-e^{-\kappa x})/2=\alpha\sinh(\kappa x),\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula \[
g_{\mbox{III}}=\beta\sinh(\kappa(x-L)),\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula \[
g_{\mbox{II}}=\gamma e^{-\kappa(x-x')}+\xi e^{+\kappa(x-x')}+\frac{1}{\kappa^{2}\Delta x}\]

\end_inset

for some constants 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha,\beta,\gamma,\xi$
\end_inset

 to be determined (since these are free parameters, we can pull out convenient
 factors of 2, 
\begin_inset Formula $e^{\kappa x'}$
\end_inset

, etcetera if we want).
 Continuity of 
\begin_inset Formula $g$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $g'$
\end_inset

 result in the following four equations: 
\begin_inset Formula \[
\alpha\sinh(\kappa x')=\gamma+\xi+\frac{1}{\kappa^{2}\Delta x}\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula \[
\kappa\alpha\cosh(\kappa x')=\kappa(\xi-\gamma)\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula \[
\beta\sinh(\kappa(x'+\Delta x-L))=\gamma e^{-\kappa\Delta x}+\xi e^{+\kappa\Delta x}+\frac{1}{\kappa^{2}\Delta x}\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula \[
\kappa\beta\cosh(\kappa(x'+\Delta x-L))=\kappa\left(\xi e^{+\kappa\Delta x}-\gamma e^{-\kappa\Delta x}\right).\]

\end_inset

Dividing the first equation by the second and the third by the fourth, and
 let 
\begin_inset Formula $x''=x'+\Delta x-L$
\end_inset

, to yield two equations for 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\xi$
\end_inset

: 
\begin_inset Formula \[
\tanh(\kappa x')=\frac{\gamma+\xi+\frac{1}{\kappa^{2}\Delta x}}{\xi-\gamma},\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula \[
\tanh(\kappa x'')=\frac{\gamma e^{-\kappa\Delta x}+\xi e^{+\kappa\Delta x}+\frac{1}{\kappa^{2}\Delta x}}{\xi e^{+\kappa\Delta x}-\gamma e^{-\kappa\Delta x}},\]

\end_inset

which (moving the denominators to the left-hand sides) becomes two linear
 equations in two unknowns.
 The first equation can be solved for 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma$
\end_inset

 to obtain: 
\begin_inset Formula \[
\gamma=\frac{\xi[\tanh(\kappa x')-1]-\frac{1}{\kappa^{2}\Delta x}}{\tanh(\kappa x')+1}=\xi T-\frac{p}{\kappa^{2}\Delta x},\]

\end_inset

defining the quantities 
\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 for convenience.
 This can be substituted into the second equation to find 
\begin_inset Formula $\xi$
\end_inset

:
\begin_inset Formula \[
\xi=\frac{1}{\kappa^{2}\Delta x}\frac{pe^{-\kappa\Delta x}[\tanh(\kappa x'')+1]-1}{e^{+\kappa\Delta x}+Te^{-\kappa\Delta x}-\tanh(\kappa x'')\left[e^{+\kappa\Delta x}-Te^{-\kappa\Delta x}\right]}.\]

\end_inset

Given 
\begin_inset Formula $\gamma$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\xi$
\end_inset

, we then immediately have 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta$
\end_inset

: 
\begin_inset Formula \[
\alpha=\frac{\xi-\gamma}{\cosh(\kappa x')},\qquad\beta=\frac{\xi e^{+\kappa\Delta x}-\gamma e^{-\kappa\Delta x}}{\cosh(\kappa x'')}.\]

\end_inset

