\series bold
Hard way:
\series default
 In the limit 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta x\to0$
\end_inset

, then many things simplify: 
\begin_inset Formula $e^{\pm\kappa\Delta x}\to1$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $x''\to x'-L$
\end_inset

, and we obtain: 
\begin_inset Formula \[
\xi\to\frac{1}{\kappa^{2}\Delta x}\frac{\frac{\tanh(\kappa x'')+1}{\tanh(\kappa x')+1}-1}{1+T-\tanh(\kappa x'')[1-T]}=\frac{1}{\kappa^{2}\Delta x}\frac{\tanh(\kappa x'')-\tanh(\kappa x')}{2\left[\tanh(\kappa x')-\tanh(\kappa x'')\right]}=-\frac{1}{2\kappa^{2}\Delta x},\]

\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula \[
\gamma\to\frac{1}{\kappa^{2}\Delta x}\frac{-\frac{1}{2}[\tanh(\kappa x')-1]-1}{\tanh(\kappa x')+1}=-\frac{1}{2\kappa^{2}\Delta x}.\]

\end_inset

Unfortunately, this is a little too simplified, because we need to compute
 
\begin_inset Formula $\xi-\gamma$
\end_inset

 to get 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta$
\end_inset

, so we need to keep the next order in the Taylor expansion (or equivalently
 apply L'Hopital's rule to get 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta$
\end_inset

).
 To get the next-order term, we expand 
\begin_inset Formula $e^{\pm\kappa\Delta x}\approx1\pm\kappa\Delta x$
\end_inset

, to obtain: 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{align*}
\xi & \approx-\frac{1}{\kappa^{2}\Delta x}\frac{(1-\kappa\Delta x)[\tanh(\kappa x'')+1]-[\tanh(\kappa x')+1]}{(1+\kappa\Delta x)[\tanh(\kappa x')+1]\,[1-\tanh(\kappa x'')]+(1-\kappa\Delta x)[\tanh(\kappa x')-1]\,[1+\tanh(\kappa x'')]}\\
 & \approx-\frac{1}{2\kappa^{2}\Delta x}-\frac{1}{2\kappa}\left[\frac{\tanh(\kappa x'')+1}{\tanh(\kappa x')-\tanh(\kappa x'')}-\frac{1-\tanh(\kappa x')\tanh(\kappa x'')}{\tanh(\kappa x')-\tanh(\kappa x'')}\right]\\
 & =-\frac{1}{2\kappa^{2}\Delta x}-\frac{1}{2\kappa}\frac{\tanh(\kappa x')+1}{\tanh(\kappa x')-\tanh(\kappa x'')}\tanh(\kappa x''),\end{align*}

\end_inset

in which case 
\begin_inset Formula \[
\gamma\approx-\frac{1}{2\kappa^{2}\Delta x}-\frac{1}{2\kappa}\frac{\tanh(\kappa x')-1}{\tanh(\kappa x')-\tanh(\kappa x'')}\tanh(\kappa x''),\]

\end_inset

and thus we obtain 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{align*}
\alpha & \to-\frac{1}{\kappa}\frac{1}{\cosh(\kappa x')\left[\tanh(\kappa x')-\tanh(\kappa x'')\right]}\tanh(\kappa x'')\\
 & =\frac{\sinh(\kappa x'')/\kappa}{\sinh(\kappa x'')\cosh(\kappa x')-\cosh(\kappa x'')\sinh(\kappa x')}\end{align*}

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula \[
\beta\to\frac{\sinh(\kappa x')/\kappa}{\sinh(\kappa x'')\cosh(\kappa x')-\cosh(\kappa x'')\sinh(\kappa x')}.\]

\end_inset


