\begin_inset Formula $-G''$
\end_inset

, leading to the equations: 
\begin_inset Formula \begin{align*}
\alpha\sinh(\kappa x') & =\beta\sinh(\kappa x'')\\
\kappa\alpha\cosh(\kappa x') & =\kappa\beta\cosh(\kappa x'')+1,\end{align*}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $x''=x'-L$
\end_inset

